Business Brief -- Greater New York Savings Bank:
   Loss in 4th Period Shrank
   From Year-Before Quarter
In addition, the bank said that as part of the order it
has been prohibited from paying dividends on its common stock
without regulatory approval. It suspended its 12-cent-a-share
dividend in January 1991.
   As for the fourth quarter, the bank's provision for
loan-loss declined to $6 million from $12.7 million in the
third quarter and $23.8 million in the year-earlier fourth
quarter. For the year, the bank posted a loss of $57.9
million, compared with a loss of $15.6 million in 1990.